    "description_long": "This object is a vintage-style radio receiver with a rectangular wooden body and a prominent black handle on top for portability. The front face is divided into two sections: the left side features a fabric-covered speaker grille, while the right side has a glossy black control panel with several round buttons and a small rectangular display. An extendable metal antenna protrudes from the top, suggesting FM/AM radio functionality. The back panel is plain with a single visible port or knob, and the sides are smooth, showcasing the wood grain. The overall design is compact, functional, and reminiscent of mid-20th-century portable radios.",
